  "prompt": "How to recover/restore imei numbers on Android erased from command \"fastboot erase all\" ?",
  "response": "Restoring or recovering IMEI numbers on an Android device that has been erased using the \"fastboot erase all\" command can be highly challenging. This command will essentially wipe all data on the device, including IMEI information stored in non-volatile storage. Here are the steps you might consider if you encounter this situation:\n\n1. **Backup:** Always keep a backup of your IMEI numbers before performing any risky operations.\n\n2. **Check Device Documentation:** Refer to your device's documentation or manufacturer's website for instructions specific to your model. Manufacturers might have different tools or procedures for restoring IMEI numbers.\n\n3. **Official Service Center:** Reach out to the official service center of your device manufacturer. They have the proper tools and expertise to restore IMEI numbers legally and safely.\n\n4. **Specialized Software:** There are specialized tools like QPST (Qualcomm Product Support Tools) or other proprietary software provided by manufacturers. Usage of these tools might require technical expertise and proper authorization.\n\n5. **Root and Custom Recovery:** If you have a rooted device with custom recovery installed (like TWRP), you might be able to restore a backup that includes the IMEI information. Note that the device needs to be rooted and you should have created a backup prior to the wipe.\n\n6. **IMEI Certificates:** In some cases, IMEI certificates are stored in special partitions of the device. If you have the certificates backed up, you can restore them using fastboot or other tools.\n\n7. **Community Forums:** Engage with community forums such as XDA Developers. There might be device-specific guides and tools shared by developers and users.\n\n8. **Legal Considerations:** Be aware that changing or restoring IMEI numbers can have legal implications. Always ensure that you are abiding by the law and not engaging in any activities that are illegal in your region.\n\nImportant Note: IMEI numbers are unique identifiers and tampering with them or using unauthorized methods to restore them can be illegal. Always follow lawful methods and seek professional help if needed.\n\nRemember, prevention is better than cure. Always make backups and thoroughly understand any command or procedure before executing it on your device.",
